To ensure effective operations in support of the Country Programme  UNICEF shifted Master Data Management to BTC/Finance with extensive data cleaning  strengthened internal and external complaint management and risk assessment  and built new procurement partnerships.

UNICEF and partners have achieved important results in improving immunization and health services  conducting a first health system evaluation and the effective implementation of the prevention of mother-to-child HIV transmission.

In 2017 UNICEF contributed to increasing equitable access to quality WASH interventions by vulnerable populations  with a special focus on facilitating access to safe drinking water to 106 709 new persons  and increasing WASH services availability and accessibility in 87 schools and 14 health facilities in deprived areas.

Demonstrates accountability and transparency in managing the resources of the office and commitment to staff safety and security. Highly resilient and effective ICT infrastructure and platforms have been implemented with a move towards use of cleaner energy.
